1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
This is a 150 gigabyte DeepSeek V4 Flash MoE model.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
It is running locally on a 64 gigabyte M1 Max.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000
The system specs, memory pressure, GPU history, and elapsed time are on screen.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Now the model is actually generating tokens from the local GGUF file.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:25,000
This part is fast-forwarded because generation is slow on a model larger than RAM.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:33,000
For this MoE model, the hard part is bringing the right expert pages into memory at the right time.

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:42,000
MoE-MADV gives macOS a MADV_WILLNEED hint after routing chooses the active experts.

8
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:50,000
On the decode benchmark, generation improved from 0.98 to 1.23 tokens per second.

9
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:56,000
That is a 25.4 percent throughput gain without changing the model.

10
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The scripts, data, and charts are on GitHub at daystar7777 slash MoE-MADV.
